<DOC><DOCNO> AP880308-0304 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-08-88 0537EST</FILEID><FIRST>d f BC-US-Scotland-Bank     03-08 0153</FIRST><SECOND>BC-US-Scotland-Bank,0158</SECOND><HEAD>Bankers Trust To Set Up Operation In Scotland</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Bankers Trust New York Corp., the nation'seighth-largest bank holding company, said Monday it will establisha major operation in Edinburgh, Scotland, to provide global custodyfacilities for British and European owners and managers of largeinvestment funds.   Scottish Office Industry Minister and Member of Parliament IanLang, said through the Scottish Development Agency here that themove is an important boost for the expanding financial servicesindustry in Scotland.   Bankers Trust already has 400 employees in Scotland through itsacquisition last August of Edinburgh-based World Markets Company,which provides global financial information services. The newoperation will add another 150 jobs.   A spokesman for the Scottish Development Agency's North Americanoffices, said that more than $158 billion in funds is managed inScotland, making it the second-largest financial services sectorbehind London in the European Economic Community.</TEXT></DOC>